<header class="header">
  <div class="logo">
    <%= link_to root_path do %>
      <h1>Recognized.io</h1>
    <% end %>
  </div>
  <%= link_to 'Blog', 'http://blog.recognized.io/', class: "blog-link" %>
  <div class="banner-text">
    <h2>Revenue Recognition for <%= image_tag "stripe-logo.png", class: "stripe-logo", alt: "stripe" %></h2>
    <h3>If your SaaS company is using subscription billing, you are most likely
      over reporting your revenue. Find out how to properly recognize your revenue
      by signing up for early access.</h3>
    <a class="beta-button" href="#signup">Sign up for the Private Beta!</a>
  </div>
</header>

<section class="common-problem">
  <div class=common-problem-text>
    <h3>A Common Problem</h3>
    <div>
      <h4>Anniversary billing is convenient for your customers, but if your company
        is not accounting for it properly you could be forced to retroactively
        change your books to comply with new <a href=" https://twitter.com/intent/follow?screen_name=recognizedio">#RevRec</a> regulations.</h4>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="trusted-solution">
  <div class="solution-text">
    <h3>A Trusted Solution</h3>
    <h4>By simply connecting your Stripe account and your accounting platform to <span class="company-name">Recognized.io</span>,
      you will be able to fully automate your revenue accounting.</h4>
    <div class="trusted-lower-text">
      <p>You will have a fully automated solution to deal with complicated
        events such as trials, discounts, and plan changes.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="demo-space">
    <div class="demo-pic-border">
      <%= image_tag "demo-pic.jpg", class: "demo-pic" %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="a-try" id="signup">
  <form id="beta-form" accept-charset="UTF-8" action="https://formkeep.com/f/80602264b68e" method="POST">
    <input type="hidden" name="utf8" value="âœ“">
    <h3>Join the Private Beta!</h3>
    <p>We're actively looking for companies to try out recognized.io. We'd love to personally walk you through our app and hear your feedback.</p>
    <div class="beta-form-fields">
      <input type="text" name="name" placeholder="Your Name">
      <input type="text" name="company" placeholder="Company">
      <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Email">
    </div>
    <div class="submit-button">
      <button>Submit</button>
    </div>
  </form>
</section>

<%= render 'shared/site_footer' %>
